caption: I order a chicken parm and I never had a  chicken like that the worse chicken I ever eat .I couldn't cut and it's  was very thin and hard ..guao $20$ for that guao I was expecting something better nice and thick and alot of cheese .I definitely don't recommend this place ....

One of the best eggplant parms I've ever had! The atmosphere is amazing and the grandma that runs the place is the sweetest lady ever! So inviting just like eating at my own grandma's house-   would return in a heartbeat!
Felt like I was eating at my grandmother's house. Food was great, service was excellent and it felt like home. Only thing it was missing was getting hit with a wooden spoon.

Cafe Gia Ristorante is a must go to restaurant in Baltimore's Little Italy. My daughter and I wanted to find a place with homemade Italian food that was not the same old heavy sauce. We also wanted to eat outside and were concerned about the weather because it was mid-March at 7 pm. I called and Gia told me they had an outside seating area with heat and it usually gets very warm so don't worry. Gia wasn't kidding, the outside area was very cute and very warm. There were so many things we wanted to try! I had the homemade Gnocchi Gorgonzola and Walnuts (with butternut squash and asparagus). My daughter had Casoncelli (stuffed pasta pillows with pork, Parmigiano and breadcrumbs in a butter, sage, and pancetta sauce). Both were beyond delicious! To end our meal we shared the chocolate creme brulee and it was fantastic! The prices are very reasonable too even with a bottle of wine. We are going back tomorrow.
Amazing food and service!!  Our server was awesome and it was such a pleasure meeting Gia the owner.  Thank you for everything!!
Food was really bland. Overpriced for what it was.
Fantastic food and friendly staff. It's the best place in Baltimore for traditional Italian food.
One of the best restaurants in Little Italy - and we’ve been to all of them. Cannot recommend enough! Lasagne, pot roast, and cauliflower carbonara to die for!
The restaurant, food and service was AMAZING! Highly recommended! You will not regret choosing this wonderful establishment!!
Gia's is an amazing spot. Great food, beautiful restaurant. It's been a staple in little Italy for many years. Stop by Pan E Vino right next door for a good refreshment.

We were in Baltimore for a few weeks, I was having surgery. My best memory will be of this restaurant and the wonderful meal we had and the great service. The owner was so very kind to us. Just letting you know when we returned home we got a new puppy and named her “Gia”. Thanks for the delicious meal and the memory. We tell everyone how beautiful this restaurant is and about the great food.

Food, vibe and service was incredibile. Nice family owned restaurant. My wife and I are coming close to eating at every Little Italy restaurant and this one may be our favorite. Try the Casoncelli and Veal Francese
Lovely restaurant. Went here for my birthday dinner. Seafood is very fresh and the ambiance is nice and fun.

Amazing hand crafted food, deserts & artwork. Rest easy to the artist who hand painted the entire building, including the beautiful tables. Gia is wonderful to talk to. This is a place that deserves your business, let them take care of you, whatever accommodations you might desire.

(Translated by Google) Pizza Margherita Yummy! Great Margherita Pizza! Thanks a lot to Gia and Jonathan, two real Italians! Whenever I'm in Baltimore I'll drop by Gia for a great meal! Merry Christmas!  (Original) Pizza Margherita Buonissima! Great Margherita Pizza! Grazie mille a Gia e Jonathan, due veri Italiani! Ogni volta che sono a Baltimora passerò da Gia per un ottimo pasto! Buon Natale!
Great food
Delicious, fantastic service, cute welcoming warm outdoor seating tent!

What a great place! I’m so glad we went here for dinner tonight. The owner was so sweet and welcoming, made us feel like family! The food was really great too. The drinks were even better, if that’s possible. The service was quick but still allowed us to enjoy our dinner. If we lived in town, this place would definitely be a regular spot. Thank you for the friendly atmosphere :)
The food, service , and outdoor atmosphere were all  great.

We really  enjoyed eating in the outdoor (yet semi enclosed) patio.  Arancini was tremendous but the bruschetta was only average.  Came for the Osso Bucco and wasn't disappointed!  Somewhat limited menu and wasn't able to order Chicken Francese (as a substitute to Veal Francese) which was available.  The staff was very apologetic (there was really no need they were understandably busy) and accommodating.  Wine was reasonably priced by the bottle and was a very good meal overall.  Will be back!
Always great food! Love the outdoor seating.
My preferred spot for delicious Italian food. Service is consistently good. The bill was decent. Menu is like a cafe in Boston I loved.
Great fast service. Outdoor dining was set up well

Went there for a birthday dinner-decor was gorgeous, food was sooo good and fresh made the bruschetta was to die for this is a must try! The waiter was so nice. Young guy with tons of personality.(forgot his name) We went for tiramisu which they didn’t have but mama Gia sent us another dessert with homemade chocolate mousse that was also delicious. Will return ❤️
Great food and ambiance.

The service was friendly and customer oriented. The food and drinks were excellent; one of the best manicotti I've had. The ambiance was perfect; my date loved everything, as well. Fairly priced dishes. The restaurant was practicing COVID safety measures. We will definately come again!
Gia's is the most amazing culinary experience from the decor to the dinner!
The food and service were both incredible, and the outdoor seating environment was really charming too.

What can I say about Cafe Gia aside from, it’s a must! The food was exceptional, the experience was even better! Genuine Italian family keeping things simple, clean, and authentic. I tried the melanzane (eggplant) parmigiana & burrata ♥️ Both were delicious. I was greeted & served by Gia, Sam, and Giovanna who were all sweethearts & you could feel “familia” in their adorable restaurant immediately. So lucky I get to live .3 miles away for the next 14 months. Will be a once a week treat for me.
A secret gem in Little Italy of Baltimore. The tiramisu is touted as the best in Little Italy, and now I see why!
Perfect what a restaurant. Try the meatballs. 😲
Delicious food, delicious wine, and a great hostest!!!
First timer went to lunch with a regular here. The pasta is all homemade. You simply must get the Tiramisu. It was the lightest and most delicately flavored I have ever had.
EXCELLENT!!

Stopped for a quick lunch very good service and excellent food!

Great service, and excellent food. Homemade pasta with creamy vodka sauce and chicken Florentine were both Incredible. My new favorite restaurant in Little Italy

(Translated by Google) Very nice place, very good service, fully recommended.  (Original) Muy lindo lugar, muy buena atención, completamente recomendable.

Amazing after game dinner! Roasted Wild boar was second to none and rockfish with lump crab imperial with an aged chianti was just what our chilled weather needs required! What a wonderful owner Gia and her mom and our awesome server did to complete our romantic sunday evening! Thank you all!
Great grilled chicken Caesar salad.
Wonderful experience! Felt like family and the best Italian I've had in Baltimore! Would recommend to anyone!
The Best!
This experience was a 10 but sadly I can only give it a 5, the food service and atmosphere was outstanding truly one of the best Italian meals i have ever had
Wonderful in every way! - the food, wine list, atmosphere and service.  It was very homey and friendly.  I can't recommend it more!

The food was absolutely delicious!  It was a busy Saturday night and we didn't have a reservation, but Gia made sure to find us a great seat.  I'm quite the picky eater, but the pasta bolognese was incredible & the cannoli was perfectly sweet.  The only thing better than the food was the service!  The bartender was so personable & made sure everything was perfect!  I believe his name was Brian.  Would definitely recommend dining here when in the mood for some great Italian food.
Great atmosphere. The food was great and our waitress was terrific. I will definitely return.
Wow loved the food here. Gnocchi with shrimp was heavenly. Seemed with crusty bread and dipping oil. Atmosphere nice and cozy. Wait staff perfect.

First time there, I had the rock fish risotto it was delicious. Can't wait to go back.
It is so charming
Excellent food

The risotto was excellent, in all it's cheesy goodness. The only let down was the rock fish, it was dry and flavorless.
Good food but very over priced for the serving sizes.
A great restaurant! Food and service was outstanding!
Amazing  food!!!! Best in Baltimore!

Ten years ago tonight I proposed to my wife at Cafe Gia’s.  Since then we have moved from Baltimore to Columbia, but still love Cafe Gia’s. At a minimum we always eat there 9/9 to celebrate. Giovanni always greats us with a hug and a kiss. Great food, the best atmosphere and a warmth like family. I love this place. You will too!

A true hidden Gem a block away from Inner Harbor. The octopus was folk tender melt in your mouth delicious. Food was fresh and amazing!

The best in Little Italy. Very authentic Sicilian dishes prepared from a family from Cefalu. The decor is so old school chic. This is our absolute favorite.  Do not pass this one up.
Food was amazing. Get the manicotti. Everything is made in house. Delicious

This is one of my favorite restaurants in Baltimore. Whenever I'm not sure of where to go out to eat, Cafe Gia is always at the top of my list. Really nice staff and great homemade pasta. When they're busy, they'll take you to the "other side" which shares the same kitchen but is a little quieter and has a different atmosphere but the food is still great!
Great atmosphere Great service Great food

Very tasty. Cute little spot perfect for a quick bite or intimate evening. I had the chicken parmigiana and was pleased.

Absolutely amazing from start to finish. Delicious, reasonably priced food with more interesting offerings than your standard "red sauce" Italian-American restaurant. We really enjoyed the panzanella salad, garganelli Siciliano and the Pizza Luca. Service was attentive and warm and everyone - especially children - are made to feel part of the family. In town for the weekend and after reading other reviews I decided to go here with the family. Great staff, great service, great atmosphere. Even with two toddlers they even recommended smaller plates for them and brought them out quickly. Will definitely come back.

The homemade pasta and meatballs were absolutely delicious. The atmosphere is nice and the staff was very kind. If we’re back in the area we would definitely return!

We really loved Cafe Gia, it is a hidden treasure in the Baltimore's little Italy. Gia was in the entry and welcome us. We were impressed with the art work and painted tables, unique and colorful! Food: Authentic and flavorful Italian food...the best Italian food in Baltimore. Frest hot Italian bread, we loved the octopus salad and the home made pasta with meatballs. Gnocchis and mussels were amazing too. Cannolis and Tiramisu..the best! Great selection of beers and spirits. Outstanding service! Reasonable prices. Only suggestion: kid menu or small plates for kiddos.
Excellent home made Italian food. Haven't tasted authentic food like this in forever.  Service was great too.  Felt like dining in your Italian Nonnas house. Old World Charm!
Charming decor and excellent lunch menu. The eggplant parm was delicious. Parking is on street, fine at lunch, but would imagine much more difficult for dinner

Food was great, service was friendly and accommodating. No 5 stars because my pasta and meatballs came with 3.5 meatballs.  Not sure what the standard would/should be (I think 5) but if it's 4 and I was given 3 and a half, that's a demerit
Hands down, the best meal I have eaten in Baltimore. Absolutely great! I had the Sicilian salad, Chicken Caprese, and tiramisu.  All were great.

We went here for a group dinner (9) people.  Gia was there and welcomed us.  Very nice woman!  We sat upstairs with the doors open and a nice breeze coming in.  We all noted the nice decor and ambiance.  And the service was great too!  5 stars all around!  And reasonably proced too!  The bill came in much less than I expected.  Let's talk about the food.  One word: AWESOME!  We ordered so many different things - appetizers, entrees, desserts.  All phenomenal.  I had the burrata and also grilled octopus apps.  Both were great and we eve ordered a 2nd burrata tonhabe more.  As an entree I ordered the Summer Carbonara.  I'd never had it like this but it was excellent!  Great flavors!!  The gelato was great and the selection of cello was the best I've seen.  We had Limoncello and Pistscchio cello.  Suffice it to say this has been the BEST restaurant in Little Italy I have been to and I and the members of my group agreed we will all be going back!
Authentic and flavorful.  Each plate showed attention to detail and revealed the thought put into the food.

This quaint restaurant in Baltimore's Little Italy was within walking distance of our Inner Harbor hotel. We started with the bruschetta, which was fresh and flavorful. I had the four cheese penne pasta as my main course. Its heaviness was offset by the crisp, light pears in the sauce. Others in my party had the meatballs and the clams in white wine sauce. We shared a bottle of wine that our server recommended. We left very full, and very satisfied!
Delicious food and great service!

I wanted to go to this restaurant after reading favorable reviews and seeing pictures of art work and painted tables.  The outside and inside are unique and colorful.  We went there for lunch ordered Gnocchi and Garlic Bread.  The menu is a little pricey but the Gnocchi was very good.  I think restaurant could do better if it had a special price lunch menu.
Loved it

The location isn't the most attractive, but the staff were so welcoming. Then to top off the experience, the food was amazing. Temperatures, textures and flavor were cooked to perfection in every plate we ordered.  I LOVE my pasta slightly undercooked to get that chewy texture, they made it perfectly.  Our 6 month old was being rowdy during the meal, the staff smiled and encouraged him every chance they had.  Very friendly and family oriented. That's why we love Italian! We will be back!
The food is perfectly seasoned and takes amazing. The server and staff would nice and the atmosphere was homey. Music was slightly jazz. Highly recommended.
Very beautiful inside and out and the food and service was great!

Cafe Gia is a hidden treasure. The quaint corner ristorante in Little Italy has spectacular food, great service and reasonable prices. If you are in a rush, go elsewhere; but if you want authentic food, prepared to your order (not mass-produced) this is a great choice. The fascinating murals are an added bonus.
Laid back, friendly place great for lunch. Food was delicious.

Walking through Little Italy in Baltimore Inner Harbor and came upon this little gem.  The food was delicious! I had the Burrata app and it was outstanding.  My husband had the grilled octopus app.  Also delicious!.  We each had a veal dish.  Veal Francese and Veal Saltimbucca.  Very fresh and the sauces were perfect.  The owner came to our table and we all chatted about Sicily!  Glad we found this spot!
It’s expensive for some, but I really really really like it. The food is so filling and they have amazing options with wild boar in it!
Really good services, the bread and the food was awesome. will recommend everyone to check it out.

My boyfriend got the brushetta and it wasn't even classic brushetta it had kapers and peppers in them with not Basil,  I got the manicotti and it was micowaved and soggy,  don't be fooled my the otter appearance you get little for your money very over priced ad well with small portions

We enjoyed the delicious food and outstanding service! 😀

Everything I have ever had at Gia’s is amazingly delicious and better than grandma’s. Best eggplant parm I have ever had. Such a perfect quaint location where you know a lot of heart goes into the food. I don’t think ive ever been here when Gia wasn’t there herself. Feels like family.

I had the pleasure of eating at Cafe Gia recently with family members prior to my daughter's graduation with a master's degree from Johns Hopkins. The menu offers great options for all sorts of tastes, the service was excellent and friendly, the ambiance is lovely, with quirky and colorful artwork adoring all walls (and tables), and owner Gia herself came to our table to check that we were having a good experience. The food was absolutely disgusting and horrid. I would rather eat prison food. We ordered lasagna and shrimp bolognese and got trash instead, you call yourself an Italian restaurant and you can't even properly make lasagna or bolognese? It's ridiculous. Cafe Gia is an absolute disgrace. I would never eat there again even if someone paid me. Not only was the food horrible, but the server was very rude and greeted us and other guests with attitude. The only reason I can even give this place one star, is because the only good thing about it was the look of the restaurant. It is actually a very cute little place and the art on the inside and outside of the restaurant was very beautiful, but the food does not live up to how beautiful this place was and how amazing Italian cuisine really is. I don't recommend Gia Little Italy 🇮🇹 for friendly dining...

A hidden gem! Walked in after 8 and was seated promptly. Had a glass of Donna Laura Chianti with a plate of gnocchi - absolutely perfect! Service was quick and friendly, owner/floor manager seated us personally. Will definitely come back again.
The food is good, the staff and the service are always excellent and accommodating. Pretty much our go-to place in Little Italy.  We like sitting outside on the upstairs balcony on nice days.
Great atmosphere, rich flavors, great neighborhood
Excellent food! Arrived with a party of 14 and they happily accommodated us.  Salmon dish was bomb dot com.
Amazing food, great atmosphere, murals are museum quality as are the painted tables.  Owner is there to great you and make you feel like part of her familia.  Love it!
Fresh food, good service, nice atmosphere.  Some dishes a bit too salty.
Delicious food and great service. We had a great birthday celebration here.

Amazing Italian restaurant in Little Italy. Everything you see here was absolutely amazing. The Bruschetta ($8) was fresh and perfectly toasted. The grilled octopus ($15) was so tender and juicy. The beef carpaccio ($14) literally melted in your mouth. It went so fast. But the main attraction of this meal was the Osso Buco ($35). I get it, $35 is a little pricey for a meal but if you get the opportunity to try it at least once, take it. If was absolutely delicious, I ate the entire thing just because of how magnificent it was. Definitely recommend Cafe Gía if you ever have the chance.
Fantastic food and friendly staff with great recommendations.
Good food

Authentic
Not only are they great people, the food and ambiance is second to none! Great family run business that stays true to their culture. Thank you for all you do!
Great food and great service. Would eat here again.

Beautiful little restaurant. We were from out of town and stumbled across Cafe Gia. The owner warmly greeted us as we entered. The wait staff was kind and did their job well. She gave us a list of local hangouts with live music. The food was delicious and wait times were short. A good representation of different Italian fare. I had gnocchi, a childhood favorite, loved every bite. Great wine and desserts.
A cute, charming, little café that serves delicious Italian comfort food. The atmosphere is relaxing and the service is great. The prices are reasonable too.
The best food in little Italy. Great ravioli, amazing seafood options and quality wine selections. The mural-sized wall art only adds to the experience.
Great homemade pasta. A little pricey for portion size.

I had a friend visiting Baltimore for the day and we got lunch together. I've never had a bad experience in Little Italy, so I picked it quite randomly (and because it was open for lunch) It was delightful. One thing I really appreciated was a wine list with descriptions. You can generally prefer pinot noir or malbec or chardonnay, but being able to read what notes and finishes each has is always helpful, especially when you're thinking of what it's going to taste like with the food you order. The burrata was very, very good and nicely complemented with the accoutrements they picked (greens, thin slices of fresh peach, and some other things. Great flavor and texture balance). I got the porcini stuffed pasta pillows and my friend got the bison and ricotta and penne (a very nice take and uptick of spaghetti and meatballs). Despite a cream sauce, the porcini stuffed pasta pillows was very good and not overly heavy. The decor is quaint and quirky. Everything is colorful and decorated, and definitely done with intent. Very Baltimore. The wait staff was very nice and attentive and answered questions. There were several window seats to look out (all taken by the time we got there) Definitely recommend, even if you're in the "not sure what to get, but want good food" mood.
the food was delicious, service friendy, & the veiw was enjoyable from the balcony.
A must!  The personal pizza for lunch and the eggplant parmesan are my favorites.

Classy but with plenty of flair and charm you would expect from a Little Italy restaurant.  I usually went during the down times so it was very quiet.  The food was great and the staff friendly.  Gia, the owner, will walk around occasssionally and talk with customers which is a nice touch.
We showed up quite late and they opened the upstairs room for the 5 of us. Food is very good: veal alla francese was to die for. Service can be slightly unprofessional (maybe we had a  new waiter)
Been here 3 times and was good everytime.  Waiter remembered the wine that was preferred after several months had passed.
Excellent food and drink. The atmosphere is very cozy. Plus, great atmosphere.

In Baltimore from the weekend and realized we were walking distance from this place. I travel a ton and can easily say this is one the best Italian meals I've ever had. Great atmosphere and service to boot! I can tell you, I'll be back.

Update 02/18:  Came back here for Valentine's and the service and food are still top notch. I had arranged to get flowers on our table prior to our arrival; however, they weren't there when we got there so I asked Ms. Gia about it. She had someone run across the street, get flowers, and surprise my date. Simply fantastic, a true gem in Baltimore.  P.S. The Gnocchi dishes here are so good! ------------------- So I went to Cafe Gia for the first time after trying over and over to get in-- there's always a wait here (and for good reason)! From the outside, Cafe Gia draws you in with its eccentric yet welcoming wall décor and murals. Once you step inside, you're invited to a small yet intimate space bustling with Italian hospitality, smells and fragrances of balsamic dressing and bursting fresh basil and pesto. The restaurant has 2 floors and has recently expanded into a bar in the back area of the restaurant. Though I was not lucky enough to get a seat upstairs, the downstairs seating area is more than adequate. Tables are pretty close together so the noise level can get high, but Cafe Gia just has a great vibe to it. Service is excellent as well and the food is some of the best you can get in Baltimore's Little Italy. I tried the Bruschetta antipasti and Chicken Fiorentina as my first entree. The Bruschetta was excellent, as the bread wasn't soggy and the tomatoes were perfectly ripe with a flavory hint of balsamic vinegar. The chicken in my entree was buttery good and melted in my mouth, alongside the side of green beans and giant potato wedges-- simply fantastic. Service was great as well, with all waiters being extremely accommodating. I'd recommend trying the Concannon Cabernet Sauvignon red wine with the chicken entree.  Prices are reasonable for the quality of the food and portions are pretty good compared to other Italian restaurants in the area.  A welcoming, quality Italian experience enveloped with a warm ambiance makes for the perfect go-to restaurant in Baltimore's hearty Italian district.

A nice small restaurant in Little Italy that offers a good selection of Italian dishes at a decent price. The atmosphere is a lot more laid back compared to other establishments in the near vicinity. The atmosphere is very homey and makes a good intimate dining experience for a couple or even for a larger group. The staff were friendly and attentive, but it can get a bit busy at certain times.

I came in with a party of 7 last night for dinner for my sister's birthday. Hubby and I parked in the parking lot about 2 blocks away and it was an easy walk to the restaurant. The homemade fettuccine was definitely the highlight of the night. Unfortunately it didn't come with my meal. I got the Eggplant Parmesan and although the eggplant was cooked well and was tasty, I found the red sauce to be overly acidic and kinda bitter. Overall, I found the food to be just average. My portion was adequate, but I found almost everyone else in our party had relatively small portions as far as Italian restaurants go.  The restaurant is small and the ambiance was fine. There is only one bathroom. And not one male and one female--there is literally one stall.  Our waitress was friendly but horrible overall. It took a LONG time for her to come by and take our orders, she never came by and asked if everything was okay, and it seemed to take forever for us to get our check at the end of the night. We decided to skip on dessert because we didn't feel like waiting another 20 minutes for the dessert menu.  There was really nothing special about this place. Just average and I won't be sad if I never go back.

I haven't had a lot of Italian, but this place is by far the best I've had. It's a tiny place in a quiet corner Little Italy section of Baltimore with nice tasteful decorations. The somewhat cramped environment with small tables don't feel unpleasant. Instead, it feels exactly like a cafe you'd find in a small town in Italy. I had the meatball sandwich, and they were the best meatballs I ever had. The bread was toasted and the whole thing came with a small salad in a spicy dressing. If I ever find myself in Baltimore again, I will definitely seek this place out again.
